    "message_1": "A salesman has to visit 5 different cities in a day for work. What is the shortest possible distance that he can travel throughout the day, assuming that each city is connected by a direct road to each other city and the distances between cities are as follows: \n\nCity 1 to City 2: 10 km\nCity 1 to City 3: 15 km\nCity 1 to City 4: 20 km\nCity 1 to City 5: 25 km\nCity 2 to City 3: 35 km\nCity 2 to City 4: 30 km\nCity 2 to City 5: 25 km\nCity 3 to City 4: 50 km\nCity 3 to City 5: 30 km\nCity 4 to City 5: 10 km\n\nWhat is the shortest distance that the salesman needs to travel to visit each city exactly once?",
